{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869622798,"sessionID":"ses_285eeeff4ffeSOiagua6Vdl75T","part":{"id":"prt_d7a13f98a0015KEoEh03gx1C3a","messageID":"msg_d7a116fea001L7k1XF465f6L5X","sessionID":"ses_285eeeff4ffeSOiagua6Vdl75T","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-3ec203b363994a01a9be7be747847064","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status Commands Design Document\n\n**AR**: AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令  \n**Module**: cmd/cli  \n**Language**: Python  \n**Size**: M\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `invoke` and `status` commands are essential components of the AgentCube CLI that enable users to interact with deployed AI agents. The `invoke` command sends requests to published agent endpoints with optional payloads and custom headers, while the `status` command provides visibility into agent deployment state and health. Both commands support multiple providers: the AgentCube custom resource (AgentRuntime CR) and standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + Service).\n\n## Background\n\nAgentCube users need to interact with their deployed AI agents after the publish process completes. This includes:\n\n1. **Invocation**: Sending requests to agents with custom payloads, managing session IDs, and receiving responses\n2. **Status Monitoring**: Checking deployment health, endpoint availability, and runtime status\n3. **Multi-provider Support**: Working with both AgentCube CRs and standard Kubernetes deployments\n4. **Flexible Configuration**: Supporting custom headers, different payload formats, and provider-specific options\n\nThe invoke/status commands complete the lifecycle management flow (pack → build → publish → invoke → status), providing users with full control over their AI agents.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐\n│   CLI (Typer)   │\n│  main.py     │\n└──────┬──────┘\n       │\n       ├──► invoke() ───► InvokeRuntime ───► HTTP Client\n       │                  invoke_runtime.py         │\n       │                                            ├──► AgentCube Provider (CR)\n       │                                            └──► Direct HTTP (K8s Service)\n       │\n       └──► status() ───► StatusRuntime ───► K8s Client\n                          status_runtime.py         │\n                                                   ├──► AgentRuntime CR Status\n                                                   └──► Deployment/Service Status\n```\n\n### Layer Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│         CLI Layer (agentcube/cli/main.py)    │\n│  • Typer command definitions               │\n│  • User input validation                   │\n│  • Rich output formatting                  │\n│  • Error handling and user feedback        │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                    │\n                    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│     Runtime Layer (agentcube/runtime/)     │\n│  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  │\n│  │  InvokeRuntime  │  │  StatusRuntime  │  │\n│  │  invoke_runtime.py││ status_runtime.py│  │\n│  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  │\n│  • Command orchestration                   │\n│  • Provider selection                      │\n│  • Session management                      │\n│  • Endpoint resolution                     │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                    │\n                    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│      Service Layer (agentcube/services/)   │\n│  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  │\n│  │AgentCubeProvider│  │KubernetesProvider│ │\n│  │agentcube_       │  │k8s_provider.py  │  │\n│  │provider.py      │  │                 │  │\n│  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  │\n│  • AgentRuntime CR operations              │\n│  • K8s Deployment/Service operations       │\n│  • Metadata management                     │\n│  • Status aggregation                      │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                    │\n                    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│    HTTP / K8s Client Layer                  │\n│  • httpx.AsyncClient (async HTTP requests) │\n│  • kubernetes.KubernetesClient (K8s API)   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Key Components\n\n1. **CLI Layer** (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n   - `invoke()`: Typer command for invoking agents\n   - `status()`: Typer command for checking agent status\n   - Payload and header parsing\n   - Provider selection\n   - Rich table formatting for status output\n\n2. **Runtime Layer**\n   - `InvokeRuntime`: Orchestration of agent invocation\n   - `StatusRuntime`: Aggregation of deployment status\n   - Provider abstraction (AgentCube vs K8s)\n   - Session ID management\n\n3. **Service Layer**\n   - `AgentCubeProvider`: AgentRuntime CR operations\n   - `KubernetesProvider`: Standard K8s deployment operations\n   - `MetadataService`: Loading workspace metadata\n\n4. **Data Plane Clients** (from Python SDK)\n   - `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`: HTTP communication with agents\n   - Session header management (`x-agentcube-session-id`)\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### InvokeOptions\n\nDictionary containing invoke command options:\n\n```python\n{\n    \"workspace\": str,                          # Path to workspace (default: \".\")\n    \"payload\": Dict[str, Any],                 # JSON payload for agent\n    \"headers\": Optional[Dict[str, str]],       # Custom HTTP headers\n    \"provider\": str,                           # \"agentcube\" or \"k8s\" (default: \"agentcube\")\n    \"verbose\": bool,                           # Enable verbose logging\n}\n```\n\n### StatusOptions\n\nDictionary containing status command options:\n\n```python\n{\n    \"workspace\": str,                          # Path to workspace (default: \".\")\n    \"provider\": str,                           # \"agentcube\" or \"k8s\" (default: \"agentcube\")\n    \"verbose\": bool,                           # Enable verbose logging\n}\n```\n\n### AgentMetadata Fields (Invoke/Status-related)\n\nRelevant fields from `AgentMetadata` for invoke/status operations:\n\n```python\nagent_name: str                          # Agent identifier\nagent_id: Optional[str]                  # Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\nagent_endpoint: Optional[str]            # Published agent endpoint URL\nsession_id: Optional[str]                # Current session ID for invoke\nk8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] # K8s deployment information\nrouter_url: Optional[str]                # Router URL for AgentCube provider\n```\n\n### K8sDeploymentInfo\n\nStructure for standard K8s deployment information:\n\n```python\n{\n    \"type\": str,                          # \"Deployment\" or \"AgentRuntime\"\n    \"namespace\": str,                     # K8s namespace\n    \"name\": str,                          # Deployment or CR name\n    \"replicas\": int,                      # Number of replicas\n    \"available_replicas\": Optional[int],  # Available replicas (K8s)\n    \"service_url\": str,                   # Service endpoint URL\n    \"node_port\": Optional[int],           # NodePort for K8s Service\n}\n```\n\n### StatusResult\n\nStructure for aggregated status information:\n\n```python\n{\n    \"status\": str,                        # \"running\", \"not_published\", \"error\", etc.\n    \"agent_name\": str,                    # Agent name\n    \"agent_id\": Optional[str],            # Agent ID (AgentCube provider)\n    \"endpoint\": str,                      # Agent endpoint URL\n    \"deployment\": Optional[K8sDeploymentInfo],  # Deployment details\n    \"error\": Optional[str],               # Error message if status is \"error\"\n    \"namespace\": str,                     # K8s namespace\n}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### InvokeRuntime()\n\n```python\ndef __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Initialize InvokeRuntime.\n\n    Args:\n        verbose: Enable verbose logging\n        provider: Target provider (\"agentcube\" or \"k8s\")\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n### InvokeRuntime.invoke()\n\n```python\ndef invoke(\n    self,\n    workspace_path: Path,\n    payload: Dict[str, Any],\n    headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n) -> Any:\n    \"\"\"\n    Invoke a deployed agent with a payload.\n\n    Args:\n        workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n        payload: JSON payload to send to agent\n        headers: Optional custom HTTP headers\n\n    Returns:\n        Agent response (JSON or raw data)\n\n    Raises:\n        ValueError: If prerequisites not met (not published, invalid endpoint)\n        RuntimeError: If invocation fails or endpoint unreachable\n        FileNotFoundError: If metadata file not found\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Load metadata from workspace\n2. Validate invoke prerequisites (agent_id or endpoint exists)\n3. Resolve endpoint based on provider and deployment type\n4. Initialize data plane client with session management\n5. Send HTTP POST request with payload and headers\n6. Parse and return response\n\n### InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites()\n\n```python\ndef _validate_invoke_prerequisites(\n    self,\n    workspace_path: Path\n) -> Tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Validate that agent is published and extract metadata.\n\n    Args:\n        workspace_path: Path to workspace\n\n    Returns:\n        Tuple of (metadata, endpoint, agent_name)\n\n    Raises:\n        ValueError: If agent not published or endpoint not found\n        FileNotFoundError: If metadata file not found\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Validation Checks**:\n1. Metadata file exists in workspace\n2. Agent is published (has `agent_id` or `agent_endpoint`)\n3. Endpoint is reachable and valid URL\n\n### InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube()\n\n```python\nasync def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(\n    self,\n    agent_id: str,\n    payload: Dict[str, Any],\n    headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n    endpoint: str,\n    workspace_path: Path\n) -> Any:\n    \"\"\"\n    Invoke agent using AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR).\n\n    Args:\n        agent_id: Agent ID from metadata\n        payload: Request payload\n        headers: Custom headers\n        endpoint: Base endpoint URL\n        workspace_path: Path to workspace (for metadata access)\n\n    Returns:\n        Agent response\n\n    Raises:\n        RuntimeError: If invocation fails\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n- Constructs AgentRuntime invocation URL: `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n- Uses `httpx.AsyncClient` for async HTTP request\n- Adds session header if `session_id` in metadata\n- Merges custom headers\n- Sends POST request with JSON payload\n- Returns parsed JSON response\n\n### InvokeRuntime._direct_http_invocation()\n\n```python\nasync def _direct_http_invocation(\n    self,\n    endpoint: str,\n    payload: Dict[str, Any],\n    headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n    workspace_path: Path\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Direct HTTP invocation to agent endpoint (K8s Service).\n\n    Args:\n        endpoint: Full endpoint URL\n        payload: Request payload\n        headers: Custom headers\n        workspace_path: Path to workspace\n\n    Returns:\n        Agent response as dictionary\n\n    Raises:\n        RuntimeError: If HTTP request fails\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n- Uses `httpx.AsyncClient` for async HTTP request\n- Adds session header if `session_id` in metadata\n- Merges custom headers\n- Sends POST request with JSON payload\n- Returns parsed JSON response\n\n### StatusRuntime()\n\n```python\ndef __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Initialize StatusRuntime.\n\n    Args:\n        verbose: Enable verbose logging\n        provider: Target provider (\"agentcube\" or \"k8s\")\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n### StatusRuntime.get_status()\n\n```python\ndef get_status(\n    self,\n    workspace_path: Path,\n    provider: Optional[str] = None\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Get the status of a deployed agent.\n\n    Args:\n        workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n        provider: Optional provider override (\"agentcube\" or \"k8s\")\n\n    Returns:\n        StatusResult dictionary with deployment status\n\n    Raises:\n        FileNotFoundError: If metadata file not found\n        RuntimeError: If status check fails\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Load metadata from workspace\n2. Check if agent is published\n3. Determine provider (from argument or metadata)\n4. Query provider-specific status\n5. Aggregate status information\n6. Return status result\n\n### StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status()\n\n```python\ndef _get_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Get status for standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service.\n\n    Args:\n        metadata: Agent metadata with deployment information\n\n    Returns:\n        StatusResult dictionary\n\n    Raises:\n        RuntimeError: If K8s API query fails\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n- Uses `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()`\n- Queries Deployment status (replicas, available_replicas)\n- Queries Service status (NodePort, endpoints)\n- Aggregates into status result\n- Determines overall status: \"running\", \"pending\", \"error\"\n\n### StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status()\n\n```python\ndef _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Get status for AgentCube AgentRuntime CR.\n\n    Args:\n        metadata: Agent metadata with CR information\n\n    Returns:\n        StatusResult dictionary\n\n    Raises:\n        RuntimeError: If CR query fails\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n- Uses `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime()`\n- Queries AgentRuntime custom resource\n- Extracts status from CR `.status` field\n- Checks `agentEndpoint` for availability\n- Determines overall status: \"running\", \"created_no_status\", \"not_found_in_k8s\", \"error\"\n\n### CLI Layer Functions\n\n#### main.invoke()\n\n```python\ndef invoke(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n    header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Invoke a published agent with a JSON payload.\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Parse payload JSON (exit with error if invalid)\n2. Parse headers from `--header` arguments (format: `key:value`)\n3. Initialize `InvokeRuntime` with provider\n4. Call `runtime.invoke()` with workspace, payload, headers\n5. Display result using Rich console\n6. Handle errors with `_handle_error()`\n\n#### main.status()\n\n```python\ndef status(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Check the status of a published agent.\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Initialize `StatusRuntime` with provider\n2. Call `runtime.get_status()` with workspace\n3. Display status in Rich table format\n4. Exit with code 1 if status is \"not_published\" or \"error\"\n5. Handle errors with `_handle_error()`\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Hierarchy\n\n```\nException\n├── ValueError (User input/prerequisite errors)\n│   ├── \"Invalid JSON payload: {error}\"\n│   ├── \"Invalid header format: {header}. Expected 'key:value'\"\n│   ├── \"Agent not published. Run 'publish' first.\"\n│   ├── \"No agent endpoint found in metadata\"\n│   └── \"Both router_url and workload_manager_url must be configured in metadata for provider=agentcube\"\n├── RuntimeError (System/runtime errors)\n│   ├── \"Failed to invoke agent: {error}\"\n│   ├── \"Agent endpoint not reachable: {endpoint}\"\n│   ├── \"Failed to get agent status: {error}\"\n│   ├── \"AgentRuntime not found in Kubernetes\"\n│   └── \"Kubernetes API error: {error}\"\n├── httpx.HTTPError (HTTP errors)\n│   ├── Connection errors\n│   ├── Timeout errors\n│   └── HTTP status errors (4xx, 5xx)\n└── FileNotFoundError\n    └── \"No metadata file found in {workspace}\"\n```\n\n### Error Handling Strategy\n\n#### CLI Layer Payload Validation\n\n```python\ndef invoke(...):\n    # Validate payload JSON\n    try:\n        payload_dict = json.loads(payload)\n    except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n        console.print(f\"[red]Invalid JSON payload: {e}[/red]\")\n        raise typer.Exit(1)\n    \n    # Validate headers format\n    headers = {}\n    if header_list:\n        for header in header_list:\n            if ':' not in header:\n                console.print(f\"[red]Invalid header format: {header}. Expected 'key:value'[/red]\")\n                raise typer.Exit(1)\n            key, value = header.split(':', 1)\n            headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n    \n    # Proceed with invocation\n    try:\n        runtime = InvokeRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n        result = runtime.invoke(workspace_path, payload_dict, headers)\n        display_result(result)\n    except Exception as e:\n        _handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)\n```\n\n#### InvokeRuntime Error Handling\n\n```python\ndef invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any:\n    try:\n        metadata, endpoint, agent_name = self._validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path)\n        \n        # Async invocation\n        result = asyncio.run(self._execute_invoke(metadata, endpoint, payload, headers))\n        return result\n    except ValueError as e:\n        raise  # Re-raise user input errors\n    except httpx.HTTPError as e:\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to invoke agent: {e}\") from e\n    except Exception as e:\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to invoke agent: {e}\") from e\n```\n\n#### StatusRuntime Error Handling\n\n```python\ndef get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    try:\n        metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n        \n        if not metadata.agent_id and not metadata.agent_endpoint:\n            return {\n                \"status\": \"not_published\",\n                \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n                \"message\": \"Agent not published. Run 'publish' first.\"\n            }\n        \n        # Provider-specific status\n        resolved_provider = provider or \"agentcube\"\n        if resolved_provider == \"agentcube\":\n            return self._get_cr_k8s_status(metadata)\n        else:\n            return self._get_k8s_status(metadata)\n    except FileNotFoundError as e:\n        raise\n    except Exception as e:\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to get agent status: {e}\") from e\n```\n\n#### HTTP Error Handling with Retries\n\n```python\nasync def _http_post_with_retry(self, url: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Dict[str, str], max_retries: int = 3) -> Any:\n    retry_count = 0\n    last_error = None\n    \n    while retry_count < max_retries:\n        try:\n            async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=self.timeout) as client:\n                response = await client.post(url, json=payload, headers=headers)\n                response.raise_for_status()\n                return response.json()\n        except httpx.ConnectError as e:\n            last_error = e\n            retry_count += 1\n            if retry_count < max_retries:\n                await asyncio.sleep(2 ** retry_count)  # Exponential backoff\n        except httpx.HTTPStatusError as e:\n            if e.response.status_code >= 500 and retry_count < max_retries:\n                last_error = e\n                retry_count += 1\n                await asyncio.sleep(2 ** retry_count)\n            else:\n                raise RuntimeError(f\"HTTP {e.response.status_code}: {e.response.text}\") from e\n    \n    raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to connect to agent endpoint after {max_retries} retries: {last_error}\")\n```\n\n### User-Facing Error Messages\n\n| Error | Message | Exit Code |\n|-------|---------|-----------|\n| Invalid JSON payload | \"Invalid JSON payload: {error}\" | 1 |\n| Invalid header format | \"Invalid header format: {header}. Expected 'key:value'\" | 1 |\n| Agent not published | \"Error invoking agent: Agent not published. Run 'publish' first.\" | 1 |\n| No endpoint | \"Error invoking agent: No agent endpoint found in metadata\" | 1 |\n| Connection failed | \"Error invoking agent: Failed to connect to agent endpoint: {endpoint}\" | 1 |\n| HTTP error | \"Error invoking agent: HTTP {status}: {message}\" | 1 |\n| Status not published | \"Error checking status: Agent not published. Run 'publish' first.\" | 1 |\n| CR not found | \"Error checking status: AgentRuntime not found in Kubernetes\" | 1 |\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### Test: InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites()\n\n```python\ndef test_validate_success_with_agent_id(tmp_path):\n    tmp_path.joinpath(\"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n        \"agent_name: test\\nentrypoint: python main.py\\nagent_id: abc123\\nagent_endpoint: http://localhost:8080\"\n    )\n    runtime = InvokeRuntime()\n    metadata, endpoint, name = runtime._validate_invoke_prerequisites(tmp_path)\n    assert metadata.agent_id == \"abc123\"\n    assert endpoint == \"http://localhost:8080\"\n    assert name == \"test\"\n\ndef test_validate_not_published(tmp_path):\n    tmp_path.joinpath(\"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n        \"agent_name: test\\nentrypoint: python main.py\"\n    )\n    runtime = InvokeRuntime()\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Agent not published\"):\n        runtime._validate_invoke_prerequisites(tmp_path)\n\ndef test_validate_no_endpoint(tmp_path):\n    tmp_path.joinpath(\"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n        \"agent_name: test\\nentrypoint: python main.py\\nagent_id: abc123\"\n    )\n    runtime = InvokeRuntime()\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"No agent endpoint found\"):\n        runtime._validate_invoke_prerequisites(tmp_path)\n```\n\n#### Test: StatusRuntime.get_status() - Not Published\n\n```python\ndef test_status_not_published(tmp_path):\n    tmp_path.joinpath(\"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n        \"agent_name: test\\nentrypoint: python main.py\"\n    )\n    runtime = StatusRuntime()\n    status = runtime.get_status(tmp_path)\n    assert status[\"status\"] == \"not_published\"\n    assert \"not published\" in status[\"message\"].lower()\n```\n\n#### Test: StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status()\n\n```python\ndef test_cr_status_running(mocker):\n    metadata = AgentMetadata(\n        agent_name=\"test\",\n        entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n        agent_id=\"abc123\",\n        k8s_deployment={\n            \"type\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n            \"name\": \"test\",\n            \"namespace\": \"default\"\n        }\n    )\n    runtime = StatusRuntime()\n    \n    mock_provider = mocker.MagicMock()\n    mock_provider.get_agent_runtime.return_value = {\n        \"metadata\": {\"name\": \"test\"},\n        \"status\": {\n            \"phase\": \"Running\",\n            \"agentEndpoint\": \"http://localhost:8080\"\n        }\n    }\n    runtime.agentcube_provider = mock_provider\n    \n    status = runtime._get_cr_k8s_status(metadata)\n    assert status[\"status\"] == \"running\"\n    assert status[\"endpoint\"] == \"http://localhost:8080\"\n\ndef test_cr_status_not_found(mocker):\n    metadata = AgentMetadata(\n        agent_name=\"test\",\n        entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n        agent_id=\"abc123\",\n        k8s_deployment={\n            \"type\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n            \"name\": \"test\",\n            \"namespace\": \"default\"\n        }\n    )\n    runtime = StatusRuntime()\n    \n    mock_provider = mocker.MagicMock()\n    mock_provider.get_agent_runtime.return_value = None\n    runtime.agentcube_provider = mock_provider\n    \n    status = runtime._get_cr_k8s_status(metadata)\n    assert status[\"status\"] == \"not_found_in_k8s\"\n```\n\n#### Test: CLI Payload Parsing\n\n```python\ndef test_invoke_valid_json():\n    # Test with valid JSON payload\n    payload_str = '{\"message\": \"hello\", \"count\": 5}'\n    payload_dict = json.loads(payload_str)\n    assert payload_dict == {\"message\": \"hello\", \"count\": 5}\n\ndef test_invoke_invalid_json():\n    # Test with invalid JSON payload\n    payload_str = '{\"message\": \"hello\", count: 5}'\n    with pytest.raises(json.JSONDecodeError):\n        json.loads(payload_str)\n\ndef test_invoke_headers_parsing():\n    # Test header parsing\n    header_list = [\"Authorization: Bearer token123\", \"Content-Type: application/json\"]\n    headers = {}\n    for header in header_list:\n        key, value = header.split(':', 1)\n        headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n    assert headers == {\n        \"Authorization\": \"Bearer token123\",\n        \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n    }\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n#### Test: End-to-End Invoke (Mocked)\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.integration\ndef test_e2e_invoke_agent(tmp_path, mocker):\n    tmp_path.joinpath(\"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n        \"agent_name: test-agent\\nentrypoint: python main.py\\nagent_id: abc123\\nagent_endpoint: http://localhost:8080\\nsession_id: session123\"\n    )\n    \n    runtime = InvokeRuntime()\n    \n    # Mock HTTP client\n    mock_response = mocker.MagicMock()\n    mock_response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"success\", \"data\": \"test response\"}\n    mock_response.raise_for_status = mocker.MagicMock()\n    \n    mock_client = mocker.patch(\"httpx.AsyncClient\")\n    mock_client.return_value.__aenter__.return_value.post.return_value = mock_response\n    \n    payload = {\"message\": \"hello\"}\n    headers = {\"X-Custom-Header\": \"value\"}\n    \n    result = runtime.invoke(tmp_path, payload, headers)\n    assert result == {\"result\": \"success\", \"data\": \"test response\"}\n```\n\n#### Test: End-to-End Status (Mocked K8s)\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.integration\ndef test_e2e_status_k8s(tmp_path, mocker):\n    tmp_path.joinpath(\"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n        \"agent_name: test-agent\\nentrypoint: python main.py\\nagent_id: abc123\\nk8s_deployment:\\n  type: Deployment\\n  name: test-agent\\n  namespace: default\\n  replicas: 2\\n  service_url: http://localhost:30080\\n\"\n    )\n    \n    runtime = StatusRuntime(provider=\"k8s\")\n    \n    # Mock K8s provider\n    mock_status = {\n        \"status\": \"running\",\n        \"agent_name\": \"test-agent\",\n        \"endpoint\": \"http://localhost:30080\",\n        \"deployment\": {\n            \"type\": \"Deployment\",\n            \"name\": \"test-agent\",\n            \"namespace\": \"default\",\n            \"replicas\": 2,\n            \"available_replicas\": 2,\n            \"service_url\": \"http://localhost:30080\",\n        }\n    }\n    \n    mocker.patch.object(runtime, \"_get_k8s_status\", return_value=mock_status)\n    \n    status = runtime.get_status(tmp_path)\n    assert status[\"status\"] == \"running\"\n    assert status[\"deployment\"][\"available_replicas\"] == 2\n```\n\n### Mocking Strategy\n\n#### HTTP Client Mock\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_http_client(mocker):\n    client = mocker.MagicMock(spec=httpx.AsyncClient)\n    \n    async def mock_post(url, json=None, headers=None, timeout=None):\n        response = mocker.MagicMock()\n        response.status_code = 200\n        response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"success\"}\n        response.raise_for_status = mocker.MagicMock()\n        return response\n    \n    client.post = mock_post\n    return client\n```\n\n#### Kubernetes Provider Mock\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_k8s_provider(mocker):\n    provider = mocker.MagicMock(spec=KubernetesProvider)\n    provider.get_agent_status.return_value = {\n        \"status\": \"running\",\n        \"deployment\": {\n            \"type\": \"Deployment\",\n            \"name\": \"test-agent\",\n            \"namespace\": \"default\",\n            \"replicas\": 2,\n            \"available_replicas\": 2,\n        }\n    }\n    return provider\n```\n\n#### AgentCube Provider Mock\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_agentcube_provider(mocker):\n    provider = mocker.MagicMock(spec=AgentCubeProvider)\n    provider.get_agent_runtime.return_value = {\n        \"metadata\": {\"name\": \"test-agent\"},\n        \"status\": {\n            \"phase\": \"Running\",\n            \"agentEndpoint\": \"http://localhost:8080\"\n        }\n    }\n    return provider\n```\n\n### Test Coverage Goals\n\n| Component | Target Coverage |\n|-----------|-----------------|\n| invoke_runtime.py | 85%+ |\n| status_runtime.py | 85%+ |\n| main.py (invoke/status commands) | 80%+ |\n| agentcube_provider.py | 80%+ (status methods) |\n| k8s_provider.py | 80%+ (status methods) |\n\n### Test Execution\n\n```bash\n# Run all tests\npytest tests/\n\n# Run with coverage\npytest --cov=agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime --cov=agentcube.runtime.status_runtime\n\n# Run integration tests only\npytest -m integration\n\n# Run unit tests only\npytest -m \"not integration\"\n\n# Run specific test file\npytest tests/test_invoke_runtime.py\n```\n\n## CLI Usage\n\n### Invoke Command\n\n#### Basic Usage\n\n```bash\n# Invoke with default payload ({})\nkubectl-agentcube invoke\n\n# Invoke with custom payload\nkubectl-agentcube invoke --payload '{\"message\": \"hello\", \"count\": 5}'\n\n# Invoke with custom headers\nkubectl-agentcube invoke --header \"Authorization: Bearer token123\" --header \"X-Custom-Header: value\"\n\n# Invoke with verbose output\nkubectl-agentcube invoke --verbose\n\n# Invoke specific workspace\nkubectl-agentcube invoke -f /path/to/workspace\n\n# Invoke with K8s provider\nkubectl-agentcube invoke --provider k8s\n```\n\n#### Complex Payload Example\n\n```bash\nkubectl-agentcube invoke --payload '{\n  \"query\": \"What is the weather today?\",\n  \"context\": {\n    \"location\": \"San Francisco\",\n    \"date\": \"2024-01-15\"\n  },\n  \"options\": {\n    \"temperature_unit\": \"fahrenheit\"\n  }\n}' --header \"X-API-Key: your-api-key\"\n```\n\n### Status Command\n\n#### Basic Usage\n\n```bash\n# Check status of agent in current workspace\nkubectl-agentcube status\n\n# Check status of specific workspace\nkubectl-agentcube status -f /path/to/workspace\n\n# Check status with K8s provider\nkubectl-agentcube status --provider k8s\n\n# Check status with verbose output\nkubectl-agentcube status --verbose\n```\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n1. **For invoke**:\n   - Agent must be published (run `publish` first)\n   - Agent endpoint must be reachable\n   - Valid metadata file must exist\n\n2. **For status**:\n   - Agent must be published (or at least have metadata)\n   - Kubernetes access configured (for provider checks)\n\n### Output Examples\n\n#### Invoke Success Output\n\n```\n✓ Agent invoked successfully\n  Response: {\"result\": \"success\", \"data\": {\"answer\": \"The weather is sunny.\"}}\n```\n\n#### Status Success Output (AgentCube Provider)\n\n```\n┏━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┳━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┓\n┃ Field              ┃ Value                              ┃\n┡━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━╇━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┩\n│ Status             │ running                            │\n│ Agent Name         │ test-agent                         │\n│ Agent ID           │ abc123                             │\n│ Endpoint           │ http://localhost:8080              │\n│ Namespace          │ default                            │\n│ Deployment Type    │ AgentRuntime CR                    │\n└────────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n#### Status Success Output (K8s Provider)\n\n```\n┏━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┳━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┓\n┃ Field              ┃ Value                              ┃\n┡━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━╇━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┩\n│ Status             │ running                            │\n│ Agent Name         │ test-agent                         │\n│ Endpoint           │ http://localhost:30080             │\n│ Namespace          │ default                            │\n│ Deployment Type    │ Deployment                         │\n│ Replicas           │ 2/2                                │\n│ Service URL        │ http://localhost:30080             │\n└────────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n#### Status Not Published Output\n\n```\n✗ Agent not published\n  Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' to deploy your agent.\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Required\n\n- `httpx>=0.24.0`: Async HTTP client for agent invocation\n- `pydantic>=2.0.0`: Data validation (via AgentMetadata)\n- `pyyaml>=6.0.0`: YAML parsing (via MetadataService)\n- `typer[all]>=0.9.0`: CLI framework\n- `rich>=13.0.0`: Rich terminal output formatting\n\n### Optional\n\n- `kubernetes>=28.0.0`: Kubernetes client for K8s provider status checks\n\n### External Dependencies\n\n- **Docker**: For local builds (not required for invoke/status)\n- **Kubernetes cluster**: For provider-based deployments\n- **AgentCube runtime**: For AgentRuntime CR support\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n1. **Streaming Responses**: Support for streaming responses from agents (Server-Sent Events, WebSocket)\n2. **Interactive Mode**: REPL-like interactive session with agents\n3. **Batch Invocation**: Invoke multiple agents in parallel\n4. **Response Formatting**: Multiple output formats (JSON, YAML, table)\n5. **History Tracking**: Track invocation history and responses\n6. **Session Management**: Enhanced session lifecycle control (create, list, delete sessions)\n7. **Timeout Control**: Configurable timeout per invocation\n8. **Retry Strategy**: Configurable retry policies for failed invocations\n9. **Status Filtering**: Filter status by namespace, labels, or other criteria\n10. **Status Watch**: Watch mode for real-time status updates\n11. **Metrics Collection**: Collect and display invocation metrics (latency, success rate)\n12. **Webhook Support**: Invoke agents via webhooks with automatic routing\n13. **Payload Templates**: Support for payload templates and variable substitution\n14. **Multi-region Support**: Invoke agents deployed in multiple regions\n15. **Load Balancing**: Distribute invocations across multiple agent instances\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Authentication**: Support for multiple auth mechanisms (Bearer token, mTLS, API keys)\n2. **Authorization**: Verify user permissions before invoking agents\n3. **Input Validation**: Strict validation of payloads to prevent injection attacks\n4. **HTTPS Enforcement**: Require HTTPS for agent endpoints in production\n5. **Secret Management**: Secure handling of authentication tokens and API keys\n6. **Session Security**: Proper session ID generation and validation\n7. **Audit Logging**: Log all invocations for security auditing\n8. **Rate Limiting**: Protect against abuse with rate limiting\n9. **CORS Configuration**: Proper CORS settings for cross-origin requests\n10. **Secure Headers**: Automatically add security headers (CSP, X-Frame-Options)\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n1. **Connection Pooling**: Reuse HTTP connections for multiple invocations\n2. **Async I/O**: Use async/await for concurrent operations\n3. **Timeout Management**: Configurable timeouts for network operations\n4. **Caching**: Cache status results to reduce K8s API calls\n5. **Batch Operations**: Support for batch status checks\n6. **Lazy Loading**: Only initialize providers when needed\n7. **Resource Cleanup**: Proper cleanup of HTTP clients and connections\n8. **Memory Management**: Efficient handling of large payloads\n9. **Compression**: Support for request/response compression\n10. **Parallel Queries**: Query multiple K8s resources in parallel\n\n## Appendix\n\n### AgentRuntime CR Reference\n\nThe AgentRuntime custom resource is defined as:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: AgentRuntime\nmetadata:\n  name: agent-name\n  namespace: default\nspec:\n  agentName: agent-name\n  image: registry.example.com/agent:latest\n  port: 8080\n  replicas: 1\n  env:\n    - name: KEY\n      value: value\n  workloadManagerURL: http://workload-manager.default.svc.cluster.local\n  routerURL: http://router.default.svc.cluster.local\n  readinessProbe:\n    path: /health\n    port: 8080\n  sessionTimeout: 15m\n  maxSessionDuration: 8h\nstatus:\n  phase: Running\n  agentEndpoint: http://agent-name.default.svc.cluster.local:8080\n  replicas: 1\n  availableReplicas: 1\n```\n\n### Status Values\n\n| Status | Description | Exit Code |\n|--------|-------------|-----------|\n| `running` | Agent is running and ready to accept requests | 0 |\n| `not_published` | Agent has not been published yet | 1 |\n| `error` | Agent is in error state | 1 |\n| `pending` | Agent is being deployed or updated | 0 |\n| `created_no_status` | AgentRuntime CR exists but has no status | 0 |\n| `not_found_in_k8s` | AgentRuntime CR not found in Kubernetes | 1 |\n\n### Session Management\n\nSession IDs are managed as follows:\n\n1. **Generation**: Session IDs are generated by the AgentCube runtime\n2. **Storage**: Session ID is stored in `metadata.session_id`\n3. **Transmission**: Session ID is sent via `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n4. **Lifecycle**: Sessions are managed by the AgentCube runtime based on TTL\n5. **Invocation**: Each invocation uses the current session ID from metadata\n\n### Provider Comparison\n\n| Feature | AgentCube Provider | K8s Provider |\n|---------|-------------------|--------------|\n| Resource Type | AgentRuntime CR | Deployment + Service |\n| Status Source | CR `.status` field | Deployment/Service status |\n| URL Construction | Router-based | Service NodePort |\n| Session Management | Built-in | Manual |\n| Scalability | Auto-scaling via AgentCube | Manual replica management |\n| Load Balancing | Router handles load | K8s Service handles load |\n| Monitoring | Integrated with AgentCube | Standard K8s metrics |","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-023/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-023/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-023/design.md","time":{"start":1775869622765,"end":1775869622793}}}}
