{"type":"text","timestamp":1775869639764,"sessionID":"ses_285eeeff4ffeSOiagua6Vdl75T","part":{"id":"prt_d7a142cfc001enp0xvAzud627d","messageID":"msg_d7a13fa40001yVWM6WRaM9JHMe","sessionID":"ses_285eeeff4ffeSOiagua6Vdl75T","type":"text","text":"I've successfully written a comprehensive design document for the AR-023 CLI invoke/status commands at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-023/design.md`.\n\nThe design document includes:\n\n- **Overview**: Description of the invoke/status commands and their role in the agent lifecycle\n- **Architecture**: Component diagrams and layer architecture showing CLI, runtime, and service layers\n- **Data Structures**: Complete specifications for InvokeOptions, StatusOptions, StatusResult, and related structures\n- **API Contracts**: Detailed method signatures for InvokeRuntime and StatusRuntime with parameter descriptions and behavior\n- **Error Handling**: Comprehensive error hierarchy with user-facing messages and handling strategies\n- **Testing Strategy**: Unit tests, integration tests, and mocking strategies with coverage goals\n- **CLI Usage**: Examples and output formats for both commands\n- **Dependencies**: Required and optional dependencies\n- **Future Enhancements**: 15 potential improvements\n- **Security & Performance**: Considerations for secure and performant implementations\n- **Appendix**: AgentRuntime CR reference, status values, session management, and provider comparison\n\nThe document follows the structure of the existing cmd/cli design.md and incorporates all specifications from the .sdd_prompt.md file.","time":{"start":1775869639762,"end":1775869639762}}}
